window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Keira soon finds herself becoming a pawn in a game she could never hope to win, and now the King on the board is a Vampire on a mission. With the only man to stop him miles away from the mountain prison in which she is kept, she must now choose which path to take in order to survive. </p><p>With enemies at all sides closing in quickly, she must tread carefully, or she might find the only man to save her isn't the White Knight she loves but the Dark King she loathes. But time with the Vampire King is dangerous, and Keira soon learns that it is more than just the power of her mind she needs to keep locked but also the power of her heart...and Lucius might just hold the key to both. </p><p>Stephanie Hudson has dreamed of being a writer ever since her obsession with reading books at an early age. What first became a quest to overcome the boundaries set against her in the form of dyslexia has turned into a life's dream. </p><p><i>The Triple Goddess</i> is her third book in the series of seven, with the story of Keira and Draven becoming ever more complicated in a world that sets them miles apart. </p>"; 
